        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 4:11PM CDT by NWS Paducah KY</headline>
        <description>At 410 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Vienna, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Vienna, Goreville, Lake Of Egypt Area, New Burnside, and Simpson.

This includes Interstate 24 in Illinois between Mile Markers 5 and
16.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
